132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1390
H.P. 912 House of Representatives, April 1, 2025
Resolve, Directing the Secretary of State to Develop a Plan for a
Multiyear Registration System for National Car Rental Companies
Reference to the Committee on Transportation suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative PARRY of Arundel.
Cosponsored by Senator NANGLE of Cumberland and
Representatives: CRAFTS of Newcastle, MASON of Lisbon, WHITE of Guilford.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Preamble. Whereas, a multiyear registration system simplifies the registration,
2 renewal and management process for entities that own and rent large numbers of motor
3 vehicles; and
4 Whereas, the Secretary of State previously developed and implemented a successful
5 long-term registration program for trailers and semitrailers nationwide pursuant to the
6 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 29-A, section 512 that has generated significant income for
7 the State; and
8 Whereas, other states have implemented a multiyear registration system for motor
9 vehicles that has simplified the registration and management of motor vehicle rentals for
10 national car rental companies in those states and in turn has generated funds in registration
11 fees and excise taxes; now, therefore, be it
12 Sec. 1. Plan for multiyear registration system. Resolved: That the Department
13 of the Secretary of State, Bureau of Motor Vehicles shall develop a plan for the creation of
14 a multiyear registration system for rental passenger vehicles. In developing this plan, the
15 bureau shall seek input from the Department of Public Safety, Bureau of State Police,
16 national car rental companies, municipalities and other relevant stakeholders and review
17 existing multiyear registration systems that have been implemented in other states.
18 Sec. 2. Submission of plan. Resolved: That the Secretary of State shall submit the
19 plan developed pursuant to section 1 along with legislation necessary to accomplish the
20 objectives outlined in the plan to the Joint Standing Committee on Transportation by
21 December 3, 2025.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This resolve requires the Department of the Secretary of State, Bureau of Motor
2244 Vehicles to develop a plan for the creation of a multiyear registration system for rental
2255 passenger vehicles. It requires the Secretary of State to submit the plan to the Joint Standing
2266 Committee on Transportation by December 3, 2025.
